{"key":"processedPost-9734500","value":{"id":9734500,"first":9734480,"last":9734647,"when":1233779357,"utime":"02/04/09 10:29 PM","content":"Oysters will grow on pf tek, but in truth it's just a novelty grow to learn the basics.&nbsp; You can't grow enough to be worth the time and money as food.&nbsp; However, you can spawn the fully colonized brf cakes to sawdust and woodchips, which is what I'd recommend to do with at least half your first batch of cakes.&nbsp; They also grow well on shredded paper, so you can score ecology points at school by recycling old tests and other paper waste from the various classes into mushrooms.<br /><br />Oysters require far more FAE than cubes, so if you use a shotgun terrarium, leave the lid off and mist more to make up for lost moisture.&nbsp; Keep them in a cool place, because oysters get thin and paper-like at room temperature.&nbsp; At 50F, they'll form nice meaty fruits that will knock your socks off in a stir fry.&nbsp; I've found that the unheated crawl space under my house is perfect for oysters in the winter.<br />RR","title":"Re: Mycology Club :)!","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}